  "decision_conditions": [
    "REASON: The proposed roof extension with terraces and associated balustrades, by reason of their inappropriate size, bulk massing, detailed design, siting above an existing mansard roof extension, would be an incongruous and dominant form of development visible from both short and longer views from the surrounding public and private realm and would harm the appearance of the host building, wider terrace and the character and appearance of the conservation area.  The proposal is contrary to policies D1, D4 and HC1 of the London Plan (2021), policies CS8 and CS9 of Islington's Core Strategy (2011), policies DM2.1 and DM2.3 of Islington's Development Management Policies (2013), and guidance within the Islington Urban Design Guide (2017), the Duncan Terrace / Colebrook Row Conservation Area Design Guidelines (2002) & The NPPF 2019."
